AGI does <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> not</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> give mana!<br>
<br>
AC really does not add much for a Wizard. There are two types of AC. Damage avoidance and damage absorbance. Wizards are WEAK in both. A Warrior is strong in damage absorbance while a Monk is strong is damage avoidance. A Monk cannot tank as well as a Warrior even tho they are the strongest in damage avoidance. A Wizard, along with other pure casters, is the weakest in both! AC will not keep you alive longer. Most likely that MoB will still quad hit you and still do max damage or close to it.<br>
<br>
HP will keep you alive longer (for a little awhile at least ...maybe long enuff for that CH - depends on # of hitpoints tho).<br>
<br>
The only stats that matter for a Wizard is INT (to 200), Resists, Mana, HPs, STR (only for carrying more gear), and STA - in order.<br>
<br>
<br>
